name: #10 PCP
description: Phencyclidine (PCP) or "angel dust" is an illegal, hallucinogenic drug that was initially used as an anesthetic agent in the 1950s and early 1960s but was then withdrawn in 1965 because of dissociative hallucinogenic effects that were often disturbing and sometimes severe and prolonged. The out-of-body intense psychological and behavioral effects of low doses of phencyclidine led to its abuse. In the late 1960s and 1970s, phencyclidine became a widely used hallucinogenic drug. The effects were often extreme, marked by acute psychosis and aggressive and violent behaviors, and overdoses led to many emergency rooms visits and deaths from status epilepticus, hyperthermia, rhabdomyolysis, and subsequent renal, respiratory and hepatic failure.
